506
01:02:25,937 --> 01:02:27,928
First they knocked 'em out,
then they knocked 'em up.

507
01:02:31,375 --> 01:02:34,105
And what's the third possibility?

508
01:02:34,178 --> 01:02:37,341
Xenogenesis.
Implantation.

509
01:02:37,415 --> 01:02:40,145
The production of an offspring
unlike that of the parent.

510
01:02:41,552 --> 01:02:43,952
Or should I say host?

511
01:03:22,860 --> 01:03:24,794
Come back to the project, Alan.

512
01:03:26,297 --> 01:03:28,231
Not just a matter
of protecting your daughter.

513
01:03:28,299 --> 01:03:32,133
As you can see,
it goes far, far beyond that.

514
01:03:36,040 --> 01:03:38,270
You have to put this
in the back of your mind.

515
01:03:38,342 --> 01:03:40,276
Don't even think about it
when you're around the children.

516
01:03:40,344 --> 01:03:43,404
- Don't ever let them know you know.
- Why didn't you tell us?

517
01:03:43,481 --> 01:03:47,281
- I mean, why didn't you warn us?
- Because I couldn't.

518
01:03:47,351 --> 01:03:51,845
Well, I couldn't. If anybody else knew,
the children would know.

519
01:03:51,922 --> 01:03:54,823
Look, I have spent years of my life
building a wall around this...

520
01:03:54,892 --> 01:03:58,658
hiding it so they couldn't read
what was in my mind.

521
01:03:58,729 --> 01:04:02,722
But as their powers grow stronger, they
just keep looking deeper and deeper.

522
01:04:02,800 --> 01:04:06,031
I need your help.
Would you please just...

523
01:04:06,103 --> 01:04:08,162
come back to the project?

524
01:04:59,957 --> 01:05:02,050
We've made our decision.

525
01:05:02,126 --> 01:05:04,993
Discussion will not
change our plans.

526
01:05:07,932 --> 01:05:11,663
We will live in the abandoned barn
outside of town.

527
01:05:12,503 --> 01:05:15,336
You will bring us supplies.

528
01:05:15,406 --> 01:05:17,397
You can't stop us, you know.

529
01:05:18,242 --> 01:05:19,834
Don't try.

530
01:05:26,584 --> 01:05:29,781
You've been discussing us
with Dr. Verner.

531
01:05:30,688 --> 01:05:32,622
What did she tell you?

532
01:05:37,027 --> 01:05:39,120
You are hiding something.

533
01:06:36,520 --> 01:06:39,182
I'm not letting you go.

534
01:06:42,226 --> 01:06:44,194
You haven't been given an option.

535
01:06:44,261 --> 01:06:46,320
Have you?

536
01:06:50,334 --> 01:06:53,565
You know, you don't always have
to do everything they tell you.

537
01:06:55,172 --> 01:06:59,632
- We are the same.
- No. You're not.

538
01:06:59,710 --> 01:07:01,610
You're David.
You're different.

539
01:07:35,212 --> 01:07:37,578
I've come to get Julie.
Have you seen her?

540
01:07:41,585 --> 01:07:43,519
Is she at the barn?

541
01:07:44,855 --> 01:07:45,913
Fine.

542
01:08:10,914 --> 01:08:14,077
Are you all right?
I'm sorry.

543
01:08:14,151 --> 01:08:16,779
You're okay, aren't ya?

544
01:08:16,854 --> 01:08:18,845
Julie doesn't want
to come with you.

545
01:08:19,690 --> 01:08:21,624
Well, damn it,
I don't care what Julie wants.

546
01:08:21,692 --> 01:08:25,059
Her mother's frantic.
I'm bringin' her home.

547
01:09:29,157 --> 01:09:32,285
Some kind of big accident, Doc,
out by the barn.

548
01:09:34,228 --> 01:09:35,490
Alan, wait!

549
01:09:35,563 --> 01:09:38,088
Alan, I was just informed...

550
01:09:38,166 --> 01:09:40,691
that the other towns with
blackout children have been destroyed.

551
01:09:40,768 --> 01:09:44,568
- What? All of them?
- Everyone, the adults and the children.

552
01:09:44,639 --> 01:09:47,437
They couldn't evacuate without
the children knowing what was happening.

553
01:09:47,508 --> 01:09:50,500
- The governments gave no warning.
- God. What about Midwich?

554
01:09:50,578 --> 01:09:52,512
I've been told to pack and get out.

555
01:09:52,580 --> 01:09:56,243
I'm leaving tonight.
Do the same. Get out while you can.

556
01:10:08,196 --> 01:10:09,629
Another man is dead.

557
01:10:15,002 --> 01:10:17,630
Why do you hate us so much, Mara?

558
01:10:17,705 --> 01:10:21,573
It isn't a matter of hate.
It is a biological obligation.

559
01:10:23,010 --> 01:10:25,911
You are thinking of
what happened to the others.

560
01:10:25,980 --> 01:10:28,574
Then our actions
shouldn't surprise you.

561
01:10:28,649 --> 01:10:33,552
We have to survive no matter what
the cost. We are the only ones left now.

562
01:10:33,621 --> 01:10:36,089
I don't see why
we can't reach an understanding.

563
01:10:36,157 --> 01:10:37,624
Why can't we just live together?

564
01:10:37,692 --> 01:10:40,490
If we coexist,
we shall dominate you.

565
01:10:40,561 --> 01:10:42,392
That is inevitable.

566
01:10:42,463 --> 01:10:45,159
Eventually you will
try to eliminate us.

567
01:10:45,233 --> 01:10:47,326
We are all creatures
of the life-force.

568
01:10:47,401 --> 01:10:50,859
Now it has set us at one another
to see who will survive.

569
01:10:52,340 --> 01:10:55,366
- That's a cruel sport.
- Life is cruelty.

570
01:10:55,443 --> 01:11:00,005
We all feed on each other, exploit
each other in some way to survive.

571
01:11:01,916 --> 01:11:03,406
I don't agree with you.

572
01:11:03,484 --> 01:11:06,715
I think that adaptation
is the key to survival.

573
01:11:06,787 --> 01:11:09,779
Cooperation and symbiosis...

574
01:11:09,857 --> 01:11:12,826
and compassion.

575
01:11:12,893 --> 01:11:16,989
Why do you think your own survival
depends upon emotion from us?

576
01:11:17,064 --> 01:11:20,591
Should we pity you?
Empathize with your plight?

577
01:11:20,668 --> 01:11:22,636
You should feel!

578
01:11:22,703 --> 01:11:24,637
You should feel something!

579
01:11:26,107 --> 01:11:28,507
Without feelings, you're nothing.

580
01:11:28,576 --> 01:11:31,101
You're just second-rate mimics
of a higher organism.

581
01:11:32,079 --> 01:11:33,569
That's right, a higher organism.

582
01:11:33,648 --> 01:11:36,515
We're your superiors
in our capacity to love.

583
01:11:36,584 --> 01:11:39,519
Without compassion,
you're a doomed species.

584
01:11:39,587 --> 01:11:42,954
Emotion is irrelevant.
It is not our nature.

585
01:11:49,930 --> 01:11:51,955
Well, I'm not so sure
you're right about that, Mara.

586
01:11:52,033 --> 01:11:54,968
Still, you are aware
of the other colonies...

587
01:11:55,036 --> 01:11:57,971
so you must be,
in some basic sense...

588
01:11:58,039 --> 01:12:00,064
aware of who...

589
01:12:00,141 --> 01:12:02,735
what we are.

590
01:12:04,211 --> 01:12:05,701
Yes.

591
01:12:05,780 --> 01:12:10,444
So the question becomes,
"Should you be allowed to live?"

592
01:12:17,625 --> 01:12:19,115
You're suddenly
thinking of an ocean.

593
01:12:24,732 --> 01:12:28,099
You're blocking your thoughts
rather effectively with this image.

594
01:12:31,305 --> 01:12:34,297
We must leave here,
spread out, disperse.

595
01:12:34,375 --> 01:12:38,505
Soon we will have reached a stage
where we can form new colonies.

596
01:12:38,579 --> 01:12:41,514
You will arrange a method
of getting us away from here.

597
01:12:43,084 --> 01:12:44,642
What if I refuse you?

598
01:12:44,719 --> 01:12:47,210
You are a prisoner
of your values...

599
01:12:47,288 --> 01:12:50,280
and you won't be able
to deceive us.

600
01:12:51,625 --> 01:12:54,594
You know that, don't you?

601
01:12:56,664 --> 01:12:59,292
Father?

602
01:13:01,402 --> 01:13:04,496
Yes, I know that.

603
01:13:04,572 --> 01:13:06,506
Make your arrangements.

604
01:13:06,574 --> 01:13:08,769
We must leave tonight.

605
01:13:35,836 --> 01:13:39,169
You're thinking
of the one who died.

606
01:13:39,240 --> 01:13:41,401
She was to be my partner.

607
01:13:43,611 --> 01:13:46,341
Yes, it's true.

608
01:13:46,414 --> 01:13:48,882
Without a mate,
you are of less importance to us.

609
01:13:49,850 --> 01:13:53,081
And your development
of emotions is disturbing.

610
01:13:56,190 --> 01:13:59,990
We can't leave you behind, David.

611
01:14:00,060 --> 01:14:02,119
It is time we resolved this.

612
01:14:42,970 --> 01:14:45,370
Hurry up!

613
01:14:45,439 --> 01:14:47,430
Begone, everyone who is proud...

614
01:14:47,508 --> 01:14:51,945
and bring him low, and tread down
the wicked where they stand!

615
01:14:52,012 --> 01:14:54,708
- This is the last of it.
- All right, get going.

616
01:14:54,782 --> 01:14:57,842
Bind their faces
in the world below.

617
01:14:57,918 --> 01:15:00,409
Then will I also
acknowledge to you...

618
01:15:00,488 --> 01:15:04,618
that your own right hand
can give you victory!

619
01:15:19,073 --> 01:15:22,065
I'm glad you're here.
I wanted to talk to you.

620
01:15:22,142 --> 01:15:25,077
I really think
that I can help you.

621
01:15:32,820 --> 01:15:35,789
Send 'em back to hell
where they belong!

622
01:15:48,569 --> 01:15:51,333
You've got to stop!
Please stop!

623
01:15:51,405 --> 01:15:53,703
You gotta stop!
Sarah, please!

624
01:16:25,806 --> 01:16:28,536
Hast thou eyes of flesh?

625
01:16:29,343 --> 01:16:32,391
Dost thou see as man sees?

626
01:19:07,245 --> 01:19:10,078
A state of emergency
has been declared.

627
01:19:10,148 --> 01:19:12,082
Please return to your homes...

628
01:19:12,150 --> 01:19:15,449
and remain there
until further notice.

629
01:19:21,259 --> 01:19:23,591
- Come here! Grab my hand, quick!
- Come on!

630
01:19:23,662 --> 01:19:28,429
Clear the streets.
Unauthorized people will be arrested.

631
01:19:32,037 --> 01:19:34,597
This is a state of emergency.

632
01:20:10,442 --> 01:20:11,909
Oh, please be home.

633
01:20:17,416 --> 01:20:19,680
The children murdered Sarah.

634
01:20:19,751 --> 01:20:22,515
Susan Verner too.
I just found her at the clinic.

635
01:20:22,587 --> 01:20:25,351
The state police are on their way
out to the barn.

636
01:20:25,424 --> 01:20:27,415
They're going after the children.
We've gotta stop them.

637
01:20:27,492 --> 01:20:30,393
No, you can't go out there.
You'll just get hurt.

638
01:20:30,462 --> 01:20:33,522
- We've gotta try!
- The state police can't do anything.

639
01:20:33,598 --> 01:20:35,828
- It'll be a bloodbath.
- We gotta try.

640
01:20:35,901 --> 01:20:38,995
No, Jill!
Now, listen to me.

641
01:20:39,070 --> 01:20:40,662
There's another way.

642
01:20:40,739 --> 01:20:43,105
Now, look, something happened today.

643
01:20:43,175 --> 01:20:45,541
I was able to block Mara
from reading my thoughts.

644
01:20:45,610 --> 01:20:46,941
How?

645
01:20:47,012 --> 01:20:49,776
I suddenly thought of the ocean.

646
01:20:49,848 --> 01:20:52,373
I suddenly saw the view
in front of our house.

647
01:20:52,451 --> 01:20:55,648
You know how Barbara and I
used to dream our dreams there?

648
01:20:55,720 --> 01:20:57,984
We used to stand
on the cliff side...

649
01:20:58,056 --> 01:21:01,787
and in front of us was something so much
more powerful than we'll ever be.

650
01:21:01,860 --> 01:21:06,126
Well, that image came to me,
and they couldn't see past it.

651
01:21:06,198 --> 01:21:09,531
I know I can do that again.
I can build a wall.

652
01:21:09,601 --> 01:21:11,865
I can build a wall
and deceive them.

653
01:21:18,777 --> 01:21:20,574
What are you gonna do?

654
01:21:23,081 --> 01:21:25,015
The only thing that we can do.

655
01:21:33,091 --> 01:21:36,857
No! Not David!

656
01:21:36,928 --> 01:21:40,227
He's not one of them! No!

657
01:22:07,058 --> 01:22:11,154
Possible 417.
All units respond and echo your 10-4.

658
01:22:18,703 --> 01:22:20,796
Multiple suspects.
Possible 417.

659
01:22:20,872 --> 01:22:23,841
All units respond
and echo your 10-4.

660
01:22:23,909 --> 01:22:25,501
41-A.

661
01:22:27,579 --> 01:22:29,513
41-A, do you copy?

662
01:22:31,116 --> 01:22:33,243
Echo, 41-A. Do you copy?

663
01:22:33,318 --> 01:22:35,616
Okay, we're in position.
Send 'em in.

664
01:22:35,687 --> 01:22:38,952
Roger, this is 2-A.
I copy. 241 in progress. Stand by.

665
01:22:57,709 --> 01:23:00,473
What are you waitin' for?
You got your orders.

666
01:23:34,412 --> 01:23:36,175
Get out!

667
01:24:49,513 --> 01:24:51,447
Oh, God.

668
01:26:31,748 --> 01:26:34,114
- More death.
- Survival.

669
01:26:43,060 --> 01:26:46,496
Tell us what arrangements
you have made for us.

670
01:26:46,563 --> 01:26:49,031
Well, I haven't had much time.

671
01:26:51,401 --> 01:26:55,565
It is 11:22.
What are you anxious about?

672
01:26:58,108 --> 01:27:00,542
The arrangements.

673
01:27:00,611 --> 01:27:03,239
Oh, yes.
Actually, I, uh...

674
01:27:03,313 --> 01:27:05,577
I left my notebook
out in the car.

675
01:27:05,649 --> 01:27:11,281
I wonder if somebody could go out and
get it from the front seat of my car.

676
01:27:26,870 --> 01:27:29,839
I am unable to see
what you're thinking.

677
01:27:29,907 --> 01:27:31,704
Well, I'm just...

678
01:27:31,775 --> 01:27:34,972
just wondering who's gonna go out
and get the notebook from my car.

679
01:27:58,569 --> 01:28:00,833
You are successfully
blocking your thoughts.

680
01:28:30,033 --> 01:28:34,333
You are thinking of a brick wall.

681
01:28:42,079 --> 01:28:45,207
Why do you keep
looking at the clock?

682
01:28:57,527 --> 01:29:01,520
- Come on. We're going now.
- Mother, no.

683
01:29:15,112 --> 01:29:16,773
Take your place.

684
01:30:02,325 --> 01:30:04,589
Stop it!
Leave her alone!

685
01:30:05,829 --> 01:30:08,093
Jill! Take him!
Go now! Go!

686
01:32:03,980 --> 01:32:05,572
Don't worry, David.

687
01:32:06,950 --> 01:32:09,817
We'll go someplace where
nobody knows who we are.

